SIMPLE: carom
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Carom
<hw>Car"om</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. corrupted fr. F.
<ets>carumboler</ets> to carom, <ets>carambolage</ets> a carom,
<ets>carambole</ets> the red ball in billiards.]</ety>
<fld>(Billiards)</fld> <def>A shot in which the ball struck with the cue
comes in contact with two or more balls on the table; a hitting of two
or more balls with the player's ball. In England it is called
<altname>cannon</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Carom</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Carom
<hw>Car"om</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <fld>(Billiards)</fld> <def>To make a
carom.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Caromel</ent>⟦br⟧
